Gazprom Will Decide on Murmansk Refinery in 2012, Interfax Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-03-24T18:07:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/gazprom-seeks-oil-tax-break-for-prirazlomnoye-field-ifx-says.html
OAO Gazprom will decide on
construction of an oil refinery in  Russia ’s northern city of
Murmansk in 2012, Interfax said, citing Alexander Mandel, the
head of Gazprom Neft Shelf.  The plant would have capacity of 5 million to 10 million
metric tons and would process crude from the Prirazlomnoye and
Dolginskoye fields, he said, according to the  news agency .
Gazprom Neft Shelf is the gas export monopoly’s arm for offshore
projects’ development.  To contact the reporter on this story:
